## Practical Checklist for HIPAA-Compliant OpenMRS on AWS

Based on today's research, here is the checklist I am building for this project:

| Control Area | Requirement | Status for This Project |
|---|---|---|
| Legal | AWS HIPAA BAA signed via AWS Artifact | To be completed |
| Encryption at Rest | RDS encryption enabled (AES-256 via KMS) | To be configured |
| Encryption at Rest | S3 server-side encryption enabled (SSE-KMS) | To be configured |
| Encryption at Rest | EBS volume encryption enabled | To be configured |
| Encryption in Transit | HTTPS enforced for all OpenMRS web traffic | To be configured |
| Encryption in Transit | SSL/TLS required for RDS connections | To be configured |
| Access Control | IAM roles with least privilege for all services | To be configured |
| Access Control | MFA enabled for all IAM users | To be configured |
| Access Control | Root account protected and not used operationally | To be configured |
| Audit Logging | CloudTrail enabled in all regions | To be configured |
| Audit Logging | CloudTrail logs stored in protected S3 bucket | To be configured |
| Network Security | RDS in private subnet with no internet access | To be configured |
| Network Security | Security groups restrict EC2 to HTTPS only | To be configured |
| Network Security | WAF deployed in front of OpenMRS application | To be configured |
| Monitoring | CloudWatch alerts for anomalous activity | To be configured |

This checklist will become a running reference as the project moves into implementation phases.

