## What I Am Still Thinking About

Something I want to understand better is key management — specifically how AWS KMS works in practice and what the implications are of using AWS-managed keys versus customer-managed keys for encrypting ePHI.

Customer-managed keys give you more control and a more detailed audit trail, but they also introduce more operational complexity. If a customer-managed key is accidentally deleted or disabled, encrypted data becomes permanently inaccessible. That is a serious availability risk for a healthcare system. I want to think more carefully about how to balance the security and compliance benefits of customer-managed keys against the operational risk of managing them incorrectly.

